data.title: My Family
data.text:
My Family Alexander BEATON was born in 1876. He died in 1907. Parents: Malcolm BEATON and Mary Ann MC CLOUD. Annie BEATON was born in 1880. She died in 1902. Parents: Malcolm BEATON and Mary Ann MC CLOUD. Annie BEATON Parents: Samuel BEATON and Fannie McNeill MYERS.

She was married to DARRACH .

Blanche BEATON Parents: Samuel BEATON and Fannie McNeill MYERS. Catherine BEATON was born in 1854 in Hunter River, Queens, PEI, Canada. She died in 1945 in Hunter River, Queens, PEI, Canada. Parents: Frederick BEATON and Flora NICHOLSON.

She was married to James PATTERSON in Hunter River, Queens, PEI, Canada. The story of the Patterson-Beaton family becomes a little confusing.

While a relative was visiting Charlottetown they visited with Florence

Silliphant Patterson who is the widow of Wellington "Will" Patterson

whom Florie, as she is known, says was the son of James Patterson who

was born in Hunter River in 1850 and passed away there in 1942.

Florie says that James' wife was Catherine Beaton born in Hunter River

in 1854 and passing away there in 1945 at the age of 91. The first

James Patterson, the native of England was probably the father of the

second James Patterson who was the husband of Catherine Beaton.

Florence Silliphant Patterson and Wellington Patterson were married

and lived in West Hollywood for a number of years. She remembers

visiting Dave and Fred in California and a bus trip they took to bisit

Fred and Eva's place up in Phelan (the desert house). She remembers

when Dave came to Hunter River in 1928 to help Mary clear titles and

dispose of her property. The old mill in the north side of Hunter

River was Patterson's. Florence and Wellington had no children.

Florie has a Silliphant relative, a well known screen writer and who

is still active in Hollywood movies and TV(this was written probably

in the early 70's or late 60's.) Children were: Wellington "Will" PATTERSON.
